WEBVTT

00:02:18.204 --> 00:02:21.174
Welcome back. And how was it?

00:02:22.609 --> 00:02:24.344
-They were just thugs!
-Nothing to do with the syndicate.

00:02:24.410 --> 00:02:25.512
-Just a salaried employee.
-They just wanted money...

00:02:25.578 --> 00:02:27.413
They went to the cops penniless!

00:02:29.582 --> 00:02:30.550
Then, what?

00:02:30.917 --> 00:02:36.356
All of you caught the criminals, but no
clue about the bounty we're really after?

00:02:56.509 --> 00:02:59.746
They still use paper
just for all the complaints.

00:02:59.812 --> 00:03:01.648
Damn it, they're just harassing us.

00:03:01.714 --> 00:03:03.416
It's a waste
of valuable resources!

00:03:03.483 --> 00:03:06.386
The e-mail server is down
from the sheer number of complaints.

00:03:06.452 --> 00:03:10.256
There is a movement out there
to sue our company for damages.

00:03:10.523 --> 00:03:13.393
What the hell
are the bounty hunters doing?

00:03:13.459 --> 00:03:15.395
We already have a huge bounty on him!

00:03:15.461 --> 00:03:16.529
Yes, however...

00:03:22.969 --> 00:03:24.237
<i>Amigo!</i>

00:03:24.304 --> 00:03:26.873
<i>All you bounty hunters in the</i>
<i>Sol system, how are y'all doing?</i>

00:03:26.940 --> 00:03:28.808
<i>Once again, it's time for </i>Big Shot!

00:03:28.875 --> 00:03:30.910
<i>We'll start with today's hot news!</i>

00:03:31.411 --> 00:03:34.514
<i>They apprehended the culprit</i>
<i>in the series of recent Gate assaults!</i>

00:03:34.581 --> 00:03:37.717
<i>Really? The bounty on him</i>
<i>was 12 million Woolongs, right?</i>

00:03:37.784 --> 00:03:40.920
<i>But the weird thing is that</i>
<i>20 culprits were apprehended!</i>

00:03:40.987 --> 00:03:42.222
<i>What do you mean?</i>

00:03:42.288 --> 00:03:45.858
<i>Apparently, they were all caught in</i>
<i>the act, but none were the mastermind.</i>

00:03:46.259 --> 00:03:49.662
<i>Then you don't get the reward</i>
<i>unless you find that mastermind?</i>

00:03:49.729 --> 00:03:50.897
<i>But of course!</i>

00:03:50.964 --> 00:03:54.400
<i>Oh, my. I feel sorry for all the guys</i>
<i>who caught the culprits!</i>

00:03:57.503 --> 00:04:01.341
Why the hell do these
thugs that normally

00:04:01.407 --> 00:04:04.310
just rob convenience stores
attack at the Gates?

00:04:04.377 --> 00:04:06.613
Maybe there are fads in crimes?

00:04:07.247 --> 00:04:11.718
Like, "Hyperspace Gates are the in thing
among today's fashion-conscious kids!"

00:04:11.784 --> 00:04:15.922
You assault at least
one Gate or something?

00:04:20.793 --> 00:04:22.262
Hey, guys.

00:04:22.795 --> 00:04:25.865
Why don't we trade the information
that we each have?

00:04:26.733 --> 00:04:28.601
And split the bounty three ways.

00:04:28.668 --> 00:04:29.769
What do you mean?

00:04:29.836 --> 00:04:31.704
You're the one that started all this,

00:04:31.804 --> 00:04:34.040
saying we should research
this case on our own.

00:04:34.307 --> 00:04:38.845
You also said that the occasional rivalry
between comrades would be good for us.

00:04:38.911 --> 00:04:41.614
Come on, did the reward amount
make you lose your memory?

00:04:41.681 --> 00:04:45.918
What? You guys were really
keen on the idea, too!

00:04:46.986 --> 00:04:50.723
After all, we all wanted
the bounty to ourselves, right?

00:05:16.783 --> 00:05:19.752
<i>In this case, all 20 cases</i>
<i>were done the same way,</i>

00:05:23.756 --> 00:05:25.758
<i>All of them infiltrated</i>
<i>the tollbooth...</i>

00:05:28.761 --> 00:05:31.564
<i>deftly attached the hacking unit...</i>

00:05:34.100 --> 00:05:37.003
<i>and in the exact moment that passing</i>
<i>ships access the tollbooth</i>

00:05:37.070 --> 00:05:38.004
<i>to pay the toll,</i>

00:05:38.071 --> 00:05:41.507
<i>they steal the entire</i>
<i>balance from the credit card.</i>

00:05:42.742 --> 00:05:46.879
<i>Furthermore, the unit automatically</i>
<i>sent the money data that it just stole.</i>

00:05:46.946 --> 00:05:50.616
<i>It immediately launders all the funds</i>
<i>in a bank on Europa,</i>

00:05:50.683 --> 00:05:53.653
<i>making it impossible</i>
<i>to track where it went.</i>

00:05:53.920 --> 00:05:57.757
<i>All the culprits that were caught</i>
<i>in the act have nothing in common.</i>

00:05:57.824 --> 00:06:01.794
<i>Age, gender, nationality,</i>
<i>religion, criminal record...</i>

00:06:02.495 --> 00:06:06.466
And on top of it, nobody has any
of the money that they supposedly stole.

00:06:06.866 --> 00:06:09.469
Well, that's about all I know.

00:06:09.836 --> 00:06:10.870
How about you?

00:06:10.937 --> 00:06:12.672
The guy that I nabbed said

00:06:12.739 --> 00:06:17.510
that he was just following instructions
from a manual he got through mail-order.

00:06:17.744 --> 00:06:21.647
Perhaps the other culprits are
reading the same manual that he was.

00:06:21.914 --> 00:06:23.116
Manual?

00:06:26.686 --> 00:06:27.620
This.

00:06:30.089 --> 00:06:32.391
"A new criminal support software.

00:06:32.859 --> 00:06:36.462
Right now, it's a real bargain.
For the low introductory price

00:06:36.529 --> 00:06:39.098
{\an8}of 30,000 Woolongs,
you too can be rich!"

00:06:40.133 --> 00:06:41.434
What the hell?

00:06:41.501 --> 00:06:43.503
It's not easy to be a thief nowadays.

00:06:44.103 --> 00:06:46.806
I'm sure there are people
who want manuals to help them.

00:06:46.973 --> 00:06:48.741
And where is this mail-order company?

00:06:48.975 --> 00:06:52.145
It's a store that's only on the net,
so I don't know where it was.

00:06:52.411 --> 00:06:54.580
Besides, the store has already closed.

00:06:56.449 --> 00:06:57.950
Spike, how about you?

00:06:58.184 --> 00:07:00.953
The hacking unit that was placed
on the Gates was something

00:07:01.020 --> 00:07:03.890
that couldn't be made unless you knew
the system really well.

00:07:04.690 --> 00:07:08.661
The mastermind's likely someone who has
some connection to the Gate Corporation.

00:07:09.128 --> 00:07:11.697
That was my hunch,
and I investigated that front.

00:07:11.764 --> 00:07:13.699
The programmers would be fishy.

00:07:14.167 --> 00:07:18.204
But the guys from the Gate Corporation
suddenly became uncooperative.

00:07:18.471 --> 00:07:21.808
It was as if they knew something,
but didn't want us to find out.

00:07:32.051 --> 00:07:32.985
Are you dead?

00:07:49.101 --> 00:07:50.036
Where were we?

00:07:51.804 --> 00:07:56.976
Well, I guess those are the only clues
we have for now.

00:07:57.543 --> 00:07:59.011
Give me that.

00:07:59.078 --> 00:08:00.079
Give me.

00:08:01.614 --> 00:08:02.849
Yeah.

00:08:07.487 --> 00:08:11.224
This is a memory cartridge
for playing chess over the net.

00:08:11.657 --> 00:08:14.060
This piece has one match in its memory.

00:08:14.660 --> 00:08:18.064
And when you push it,
it connects to the net.

00:08:19.599 --> 00:08:20.533
See?

00:08:21.601 --> 00:08:24.837
And this has something
to do with this incident?

00:08:25.004 --> 00:08:26.572
Nothing at all.

00:08:27.840 --> 00:08:30.977
Maybe all of this is a game.

00:08:31.878 --> 00:08:34.280
For now, continue playing
that game with the opponent.

00:08:34.547 --> 00:08:35.214
Yup.

00:08:35.281 --> 00:08:37.283
I'll go talk to the corporation once more.

00:08:37.550 --> 00:08:38.818
Lesse.

00:08:39.952 --> 00:08:43.689
Eenie, meenie, miny, moe.

00:08:46.192 --> 00:08:47.727
Play ball!

00:09:05.978 --> 00:09:09.582
Another bounty hunter?
I don't care, send him back.

00:09:09.649 --> 00:09:13.619
But he's asking about
a chess-loving programmer.

00:09:13.686 --> 00:09:14.554
What?

00:09:16.622 --> 00:09:17.557
Jet!

00:09:21.027 --> 00:09:23.162
What, Jonathan,
were you another one

00:09:23.229 --> 00:09:25.898
that went through all the trouble
to get nothing?

00:09:28.668 --> 00:09:30.903
This thing isn't that easy.

00:09:33.739 --> 00:09:36.242
I believe we have given
out all the information.

00:09:37.610 --> 00:09:39.745
What more are you saying
you would like to know?

00:09:44.150 --> 00:09:46.819
Sorry, but there is no smoking
allowed in this building.

00:09:46.886 --> 00:09:49.055
I'm so sorry.

00:09:50.156 --> 00:09:53.059
Actually I had something
that I wanted you to see.

00:09:53.125 --> 00:09:54.160
What is it?

00:09:57.763 --> 00:09:59.832
This is a planned game.

00:10:00.800 --> 00:10:03.970
You guys at the Gate Corporation
should know what this means.

00:10:04.770 --> 00:10:10.042
I mean, to put a bounty on a mastermind
that we aren't even sure exists

00:10:11.143 --> 00:10:15.848
suggests that it's someone you don't
want the police to know about, no?

00:10:18.951 --> 00:10:21.887
Bounty hunters should just look
for their bounties.

00:10:22.955 --> 00:10:25.691
I don't know who you are,
and whether you used to work for

00:10:25.758 --> 00:10:28.227
the ISSP, but it's better for you
to not make inquiries.

00:10:29.695 --> 00:10:30.396
He's going home.

00:10:30.663 --> 00:10:32.832
Make sure he is kindly escorted
out of here.

00:10:40.673 --> 00:10:42.408
Damn this old piece of shit!

00:10:43.175 --> 00:10:45.411
<i>I believe our risk is too great.</i>

00:10:45.678 --> 00:10:47.747
<i>If that gets out to</i>
<i>the general public...</i>

00:10:48.748 --> 00:10:50.016
<i>I am fully aware of our risk.</i>

00:10:51.083 --> 00:10:53.786
<i>If we don't catch him,</i>
<i>the situation will just get worse.</i>

00:10:54.687 --> 00:10:58.224
<i>But why is a ghost from 50 years ago</i>
<i>coming back now?</i>

00:10:58.991 --> 00:11:01.827
<i>To think that he gave</i>
<i>everyone a chess piece...</i>

00:11:03.029 --> 00:11:04.897
<i>Chessmaster Hex.</i>

00:11:05.765 --> 00:11:08.901
<i>So, it is a game that he set up.</i>

00:11:10.002 --> 00:11:12.438
Chessmaster Hex.

00:11:45.237 --> 00:11:48.340
No good. This doesn't have anything
other than chess data in it.

00:11:48.874 --> 00:11:50.943
I wonder what they were going
to do with this.

00:11:52.178 --> 00:11:56.415
If there is no meaning to the content,
maybe the pieces are the message.

00:11:58.417 --> 00:12:00.753
Great, great!

00:12:07.259 --> 00:12:10.329
{\an8}<i>Spike, I have a name.</i>
<i>Can you investigate the guy?</i>

00:12:11.797 --> 00:12:14.333
<i>He might be the mastermind</i>
<i>behind this whole thing.</i>

00:12:14.900 --> 00:12:15.768
Hey, Ed.

00:12:15.835 --> 00:12:17.470
Ed's really busy right now.

00:12:26.745 --> 00:12:27.813
Here, here!

00:12:28.047 --> 00:12:29.815
Checkmate!

00:12:31.383 --> 00:12:33.018
Or so you thought!

00:12:33.085 --> 00:12:35.187
I'll fork the king and the rook!

00:12:42.194 --> 00:12:46.799
Indeed! This is either
an idiot or a genius!

00:12:46.866 --> 00:12:48.467
I like this chap!

00:12:51.270 --> 00:12:54.974
Chessmaster Hex.
Estimated to be 98 years old.

00:12:55.941 --> 00:12:59.378
A programmer that had been
dubbed a genius from his teens.

00:12:59.445 --> 00:13:04.783
In the Cosmo-net chess tournaments, he
dominated the champion's seat for decades.

00:13:04.850 --> 00:13:09.155
He began work on the Hyperspace Gate
control program when he was 30

00:13:09.221 --> 00:13:13.559
and created the central control
system that all Gates use to this day.

00:13:14.994 --> 00:13:17.363
However, that was his fatal error.

00:13:18.531 --> 00:13:21.000
He doubted the safety
of the Gates he helped create

00:13:21.066 --> 00:13:23.135
and was against putting
them to practical use.

00:13:23.202 --> 00:13:25.137
He was banned
from the Gate Corporation.

00:13:25.204 --> 00:13:27.473
His whereabouts
have been unknown for 50 years.

00:13:27.540 --> 00:13:30.476
So, he's the mastermind behind
our current string of crimes.

00:13:30.543 --> 00:13:31.443
What do you mean?

00:13:31.510 --> 00:13:35.247
I mean, why is he seeking revenge
50 years after the fact?

00:13:35.481 --> 00:13:38.050
If we figure out where he is,
we'll know for sure.

00:13:38.117 --> 00:13:39.051
Hey, Ed.

00:13:39.118 --> 00:13:41.053
Ed's really busy right now.

00:13:41.120 --> 00:13:43.556
Hey, you, quit playing games
and help out a little.

00:13:47.960 --> 00:13:51.330
Ed, we want to figure out
where a guy named Hex is.

00:13:51.397 --> 00:13:55.201
Hex... Hex... The Chessmaster?

00:13:55.334 --> 00:13:57.503
That's who I'm playing
chess against right now!

00:14:11.483 --> 00:14:15.321
We're almost at the location we got from
the trace we did on Ed's chess opponent.

00:14:16.155 --> 00:14:17.223
You guys standing by?

00:14:18.023 --> 00:14:19.158
I really don't like this.

00:14:19.391 --> 00:14:22.027
I mean, he's basically giving
us his exact location.

00:14:22.094 --> 00:14:24.530
Can we even trust that trace
in the first place?

00:14:24.597 --> 00:14:29.034
-You think he'd be in a dump like this?
-No, I think it was...that.

00:14:31.070 --> 00:14:34.039
<i>I heard there was a place</i>
<i>where all the scrapped remains of</i>

00:14:34.106 --> 00:14:39.478
<i>obsolete Gates were gathered along with</i>
<i>scrap metal and abandoned spaceships</i>

00:14:39.545 --> 00:14:43.048
<i>and that there were people</i>
<i>that started living there.</i>

00:14:43.515 --> 00:14:46.051
<i>Why the hell do they want</i>
<i>to live here of all places?</i>

00:14:46.118 --> 00:14:49.088
<i>That area has no nationality,</i>
<i>nor a government.</i>

00:14:49.154 --> 00:14:51.023
<i>You don't have to pay taxes,</i>

00:14:51.090 --> 00:14:53.125
<i>and there are no cops.</i>

00:14:53.192 --> 00:14:57.029
<i>I see. It's the perfect</i>
<i>place to hide yourself.</i>

00:15:11.443 --> 00:15:12.678
<i>It might be a trap...</i>

00:15:13.078 --> 00:15:15.147
<i>This might be the continuation</i>
<i>of the game.</i>

00:15:15.915 --> 00:15:17.149
Whatever happens, happens.

00:16:07.132 --> 00:16:08.200
Looks like we have air.

00:16:09.435 --> 00:16:10.970
<i>Then there is someone here.</i>

00:16:14.673 --> 00:16:15.975
<i>Yo, Jet.</i>

00:16:16.041 --> 00:16:17.042
Jonathan!

00:16:17.109 --> 00:16:18.978
How the hell did you get here?

00:16:19.645 --> 00:16:21.580
<i>Thanks for leading the way.</i>

00:16:21.647 --> 00:16:24.350
You were following us
the whole time?

00:16:24.717 --> 00:16:28.721
<i>Tough luck for you, but I have</i>
<i>important business with that guy.</i>

00:16:38.397 --> 00:16:39.732
<i>So, I'll be going ahead.</i>

00:17:13.098 --> 00:17:14.033
What the...?

00:17:29.581 --> 00:17:30.516
How the hell...?

00:17:41.093 --> 00:17:41.760
What is this?

00:17:47.599 --> 00:17:48.500
What is this?

00:18:03.415 --> 00:18:04.283
Hi!

00:18:04.817 --> 00:18:06.685
Peace to the world.

00:18:06.752 --> 00:18:08.687
And love to my bank account!

00:18:08.754 --> 00:18:09.688
You want one?

00:18:14.393 --> 00:18:16.095
Wow! Amazing!

00:18:27.439 --> 00:18:29.108
Chessmaster Hex?

00:18:29.174 --> 00:18:31.276
All right, give up!

00:18:32.377 --> 00:18:33.812
You guys.

00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:37.516
Can you be a little quieter?

00:18:39.551 --> 00:18:40.886
Old man!

00:18:43.155 --> 00:18:44.556
Don't joke with me!

00:18:45.124 --> 00:18:46.258
Hey, wait a minute.

00:18:46.325 --> 00:18:48.560
You won't get away with pretending
to be senile!

00:18:48.627 --> 00:18:49.561
Who are you?

00:18:49.628 --> 00:18:51.630
If you don't hand over
the money you stole,

00:18:51.697 --> 00:18:53.799
you'll get a nice hole in your brain!

00:18:55.400 --> 00:18:57.569
That's a big tube you got there.

00:18:58.170 --> 00:18:59.838
Hey, what are you doing, Hex?

00:19:00.572 --> 00:19:03.909
You gotta hear this. It's my first
formidable opponent in quite a while!

00:19:04.176 --> 00:19:07.412
Must be some player
if you have trouble winning!

00:19:07.479 --> 00:19:09.781
But before that, where's lunch?

00:19:09.848 --> 00:19:12.184
What are you saying?
You just ate a while back!

00:19:12.251 --> 00:19:13.619
Oh, is that so?

00:19:13.685 --> 00:19:16.688
-Really, you've lost so much of your mind
-Who are these guys?

00:19:16.755 --> 00:19:19.591
-that all you do is play!
-Don't know. But this old fogey...

00:19:19.658 --> 00:19:24.396
-Have you lost it?
-Like you can speak...

00:19:24.930 --> 00:19:27.900
To think my life savings
are never coming back.

00:19:28.233 --> 00:19:29.368
Damn... Goddamn it.

00:19:29.434 --> 00:19:32.704
Anyone and everyone,
you and that guy over there.

00:19:33.539 --> 00:19:35.908
The world is all a mistake!

00:19:49.721 --> 00:19:53.759
What are we gonna do?
This old man doesn't seem

00:19:53.825 --> 00:19:56.695
to remember anything about
yesterday, let alone 50 years ago!

00:19:57.563 --> 00:19:58.530
That's right.

00:19:58.964 --> 00:20:00.632
Hex is no longer here.

00:20:01.400 --> 00:20:05.270
Here we merely have an old man
that loves games.

00:20:08.240 --> 00:20:11.977
Back then, Hex was riled up
for revenge, and planned this all out.

00:20:12.244 --> 00:20:16.215
He made it so that this incident
would happen 50 years later

00:20:16.281 --> 00:20:19.618
during the one moment that the Gate
program gets automatically updated.

00:20:20.219 --> 00:20:23.222
Even making those that
physically commit the crime

00:20:23.288 --> 00:20:25.657
hold chess pieces to hint
that it was his doing.

00:20:27.426 --> 00:20:30.429
However, to that old-timer,
50 years was too long.

00:20:30.696 --> 00:20:32.431
He went senile,

00:20:32.531 --> 00:20:35.767
and completely forgot about
the traps that he himself had set.

00:20:37.236 --> 00:20:40.772
Well, it works out better
for you this way.

00:20:41.540 --> 00:20:43.609
Because now you don't
have to worry about

00:20:43.675 --> 00:20:46.278
the fundamental defect
in the Gates leaking out.

00:20:47.613 --> 00:20:52.517
Although the price you paid was
that we learned about that defect.

00:20:53.318 --> 00:20:54.953
What do you want? Money?

00:20:55.454 --> 00:20:59.891
Or are you planning to leak
this information to the press?

00:21:02.894 --> 00:21:05.597
Just leave that old guy alone.

00:21:06.465 --> 00:21:07.766
That's all I want.

00:21:09.768 --> 00:21:10.969
It's a good deal, isn't it?

00:21:12.704 --> 00:21:17.609
Ed would get lonely
if she lost her chess partner.

00:21:23.849 --> 00:21:25.717
You're playing that thing again?

00:21:25.784 --> 00:21:28.720
Not again. Still.

00:21:28.787 --> 00:21:29.921
Still?

00:21:30.555 --> 00:21:32.524
You've been playing that thing all week?!

00:21:32.591 --> 00:21:33.525
Yeah.

00:21:34.326 --> 00:21:35.027
I see.

00:21:35.627 --> 00:21:37.496
Well, good luck.

00:21:40.999 --> 00:21:43.769
Yo, newcomer. You seem happy today.

00:21:43.835 --> 00:21:44.770
Hi!

00:21:44.836 --> 00:21:47.306
He's a really easygoing fellow, isn't he?

00:21:47.372 --> 00:21:48.674
That he is.

00:21:49.741 --> 00:21:52.077
Checkmate.

00:21:59.518 --> 00:22:01.553
I lost.

00:22:45.497 --> 00:22:50.535
<i>Too much time has passed by</i>

00:22:50.869 --> 00:22:55.440
<i>To lament that we were deeply in love</i>

00:22:57.442 --> 00:23:02.481
<i>The wind keeps blowing, while my heart</i>

00:23:03.515 --> 00:23:07.886
<i>Cannot heal all the tears in it</i>

00:23:09.855 --> 00:23:16.862
<i>Someone cry for me with parched eyes.</i>

00:23:20.499 --> 00:23:23.602
<i>The real folk blues</i>

00:23:24.035 --> 00:23:27.139
<i>I only want to know</i>

00:23:28.039 --> 00:23:32.110
<i>What true sadness is</i>

00:23:32.177 --> 00:23:35.113
<i>Sitting in muddy water</i>

00:23:36.014 --> 00:23:38.550
<i>Isn't such a bad life</i>

00:23:39.818 --> 00:23:46.825
<i>If it ends</i>

00:23:49.661 --> 00:23:52.864
<i>After the first time</i>

00:24:10.682 --> 00:24:12.884
<i>Love. It is to believe everything.</i>

00:24:12.951 --> 00:24:14.152
<i>Hey, now, are you serious?</i>

00:24:14.219 --> 00:24:16.454
<i>Love. It is the heart</i>
<i>that provides for all.</i>

00:24:16.521 --> 00:24:18.490
<i>Come on, was that what</i>
<i>the story was about?</i>

00:24:18.557 --> 00:24:20.625
<i>Love. It is the heart</i>
<i>that accepts everything.</i>

00:24:20.692 --> 00:24:24.663
<i>-You know, this is getting fishy.</i>
<i>-Whitney. You loved me that much.</i>

00:24:24.729 --> 00:24:27.032
<i>You really can't trust</i>
<i>the previews on this show.</i>

00:24:27.098 --> 00:24:29.601
<i>A romantic love story</i>
<i>for all you lovers.</i>

00:24:29.968 --> 00:24:32.504
<i>Next episode: "My Funny Valentine."</i>

00:24:32.571 --> 00:24:33.505
<i>I'm sure it's a lie.</i>

00:24:33.572 --> 00:24:35.006
<i>Yeah, a lie. A lie.</i>

